  "title": "Reconciliation system developer",
  "description": "<p>TLM Smartstream application development and reconciliation automation for a large bank in Singapore.<br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><a href=\"https://luxhire.luxoft.com/hr/browse/VR-120474#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><br /></a>• Configure and manage reconciliation processes for TLM Smart stream application & reconciliation automation<br />• Set up and maintain reconciliations between application & external systems<br />• Coordinate & work with users/project team to design, build, test and deliver the solutions<br />• Create and maintain documentation<br />• Execute the unit testing, system integration & user acceptance testing<br />• Configuration/code management and maintenance of dev/test environment<br />• Follow the delivery governance model and regular updates to project & Business stakeholders<br /><br /><strong>Mandatory Skills Description:</strong><br /><a href=\"https://luxhire.luxoft.com/hr/browse/VR-120474#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"></a>- 4-8 years of relevant experience with Reconciliation system.<br />- Experience on any Reconciliation system, e.g. Gresham, Intellimatch, FIS (formerly SunGard), Fiserv Frontier Reconciliation, BlackLine, AutoRek, Duco, Oracle Financial Services Reconciliation, Broadridge<br />- Good knowledge of a RDBMS in particular at least one of Oracle, Sybase & SQL Server.<br />- Good knowledge of at least two operating systems including Windows, Unix, and/or LINUX<br />- Good solution configuration/ implementation skills including the ability to configure business applications using front end tools, database table updates, and data transformation tools (ETL).<br />- Experience in unit testing, system integration & user acceptance testing<br />- Writing test case, test design and configuration/code management and maintenance of dev/test environment<br />- Good communication skills and stakeholder management<br /><br /><strong>Nice-to-Have Skills Description:</strong><br />TLM, Informatica power center</p>",
